abstract: How Americans learned to live with endless wars.
snippet: How Americans learned to live with endless wars.
lead_paragraph: In fighting successfully to publish documents showing that United States officialdom has been telling lies for years about our military endeavors in Afghanistan, The Washington Post has shown how little has changed since the Vietnam era — and yet also how much more sustainable, strangely, our own era’s quagmires seem to be.

headline_main: Lies Have Kept Us in Afghanistan. But the Truth May Not Set Us Free.

lead_paragraph: Gail Collins: Bret, how do you feel about billionaires? Not personally — I’m sure some of your best friends are billionaires — but as presidential candidates. Ever since Michael Bloomberg started running, there’s been a lot of complaining about rich guys trying to buy the race. Does that worry you, or do you find people like Bloomberg and Tom Steyer to be, um, valuable additions?

abstract: There was a time in America when being called a socialist could end a political career. Not anymore.
snippet: There was a time in America when being called a socialist could end a political career. Not anymore.
lead_paragraph: As the Democratic primary elections get closer, the party leadership has begun to fret in public about universal health care and other ambitious proposals. Even former President Barack Obama tried to assuage donors’ fears in November when he said that the “average American” doesn’t think we need to “tear down the system and remake it.” His comment captured the essence of tensions that have roiled the party for months. Party elites believe focusing squarely on President Trump’s record will end his presidency, while others counter that the Democrats also have to champion bold policies.

abstract: Arab Gulf leaders gathered in Saudi Arabia on Tuesday for an annual summit that was intended to showcase their unity in the face of shared threats. But looming over the meeting were their frayed ties and heightened worries about Iran.
snippet: Arab Gulf leaders gathered in Saudi Arabia on Tuesday for an annual summit that was intended to showcase their unity in the face of shared threats. But looming over the meeting were their frayed ties and heightened worries about Iran.
lead_paragraph: RIYADH, Saudi Arabia — Arab Gulf leaders gathered in Saudi Arabia on Tuesday for an annual summit that was intended to showcase their unity in the face of shared threats. But looming over the meeting were their frayed ties and heightened worries about Iran.
headline_main: Gulf Leaders Meet in Saudi Arabia Under Looming Iran Threat
headline_print_headline: Gulf Leaders Meet in Saudi Arabia Under Looming Iran Threat

abstract: Argentina's Peronist leader, Alberto Fernandez, was sworn in as president on Tuesday, marking a shift to the left for Latin America's No. 3 economy as the country fights rampant inflation, credit default fears and rising poverty.
snippet: Argentina's Peronist leader, Alberto Fernandez, was sworn in as president on Tuesday, marking a shift to the left for Latin America's No. 3 economy as the country fights rampant inflation, credit default fears and rising poverty.
lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES — Argentina's Peronist leader, Alberto Fernandez, was sworn in as president on Tuesday, marking a shift to the left for Latin America's No. 3 economy as the country fights rampant inflation, credit default fears and rising poverty.
headline_main: Argentina's Peronist Left Returns as Fernandez Is Sworn In
headline_print_headline: Argentina's Peronist Left Returns as Fernandez Is Sworn In

abstract: Malaysia's Mahathir Mohamad, the world's oldest prime minister, promised on Tuesday to hand over power to anointed successor Anwar Ibrahim in spite of new sexual assault allegations against him.
snippet: Malaysia's Mahathir Mohamad, the world's oldest prime minister, promised on Tuesday to hand over power to anointed successor Anwar Ibrahim in spite of new sexual assault allegations against him.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysia's Mahathir Mohamad, the world's oldest prime minister, promised on Tuesday to hand over power to anointed successor Anwar Ibrahim in spite of new sexual assault allegations against him.
headline_main: Exclusive: Malaysia's Mahathir Pledges to Step Down for Anwar, but Not Before November
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: Malaysia's Mahathir Pledges to Step Down for Anwar, but Not Before November

abstract: Sterling edged higher on Tuesday, cementing recent gains as traders shrugged off weak economic growth data and kept an eye on the final days of campaigning before Britain's general election on Thursday.
snippet: Sterling edged higher on Tuesday, cementing recent gains as traders shrugged off weak economic growth data and kept an eye on the final days of campaigning before Britain's general election on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Sterling edged higher on Tuesday, cementing recent gains as traders shrugged off weak economic growth data and kept an eye on the final days of campaigning before Britain's general election on Thursday.
headline_main: Sterling Shrugs Off Weak GDP Data, Cements Gains Before Election
headline_print_headline: Sterling Shrugs Off Weak GDP Data, Cements Gains Before Election

abstract: EU antitrust regulators are considering taking a tougher line against tech giants by forcing them to do more to ensure a level playing field, a senior European Commission official said on Tuesday, a move which could affect Facebook, Amazon, Apple and Google.
snippet: EU antitrust regulators are considering taking a tougher line against tech giants by forcing them to do more to ensure a level playing field, a senior European Commission official said on Tuesday, a move which could affect Facebook, Amazon, Apple ...
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — EU antitrust regulators are considering taking a tougher line against tech giants by forcing them to do more to ensure a level playing field, a senior European Commission official said on Tuesday, a move which could affect Facebook, Amazon, Apple and Google.
headline_main: EU Antitrust Regulators Mull Tougher Line Against Tech Giants
headline_print_headline: EU Antitrust Regulators Mull Tougher Line Against Tech Giants
